-- Natori Won't Sponsor Nagoya Sumo Tournament Because of Gambling Scandal
-- Naoko Fujimura
-- 2010-06-29T23:06:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/natori-won-t-sponsor-nagoya-sumo-tournament-because-of-gambling-scandal.html

          
          
             Natori Co., a Japanese foodmaker,
said it won’t sponsor next month’s sumo tournament in Nagoya
because of a gambling problem among some wrestlers and sumo
association members.  
 The Tokyo-based company made the announcement on a
statement on its website.  
